rotect its surfaces with a suitable cloth or tape to prevent scratching.","Turn the spring pre-load adjuster fully anti-clockwise to the softest setting. Make a note of the number of turns to ensure the setting is retained on re-assembly.","Spring pre-load adjuster","Compression/rebound adjuster","Do not change the fork adjustment settings.","If they are changed, this will change the handling of the motorcycle from those which the rider is used to.","Riding with unfamiliar fork settings may cause unexpected handling characteristics leading to loss of motorcycle control and an accident.","When securing the fork in ","service tool T3880171",", take great care not to over tighten the clamp as this will cause the fork tube to distort beyond repair.","Using ","service tool T3880171"," clamp the fork outer tube, and using ","service tool T3880341"," unscrew the top cap from the outer tube.","T3880341 - Top Nut Socket","Top cap","Outer tube","Use a suitable 17 mm socket to hold the top cap and use ","service tool T3880342"," to loosen the lock nut then remove the top cap.","T3880342 - 17 mm U-Spanner","Top cap","Lock nut","Remove the lock nut, upper seat and the spring.","Lock nut","Upper seat","Spring","Note the orientation of the spring for installation. A marking is visible at the top of the spring.","Using a length of steel wire with a hook in one end, remove the spring spacer.","Spring spacer","Outer tube","Remove the fork from ","service tool T3880171",".","Holding the inner and outer tubes together, invert the fork and pour out the fork oil into a suitable container. Pump the damper rod to remove all the oil.","Rehold the fork using ","service tool T3880171",".","Carefully separate the inner and outer tube leaving the seals and bushes in place on the outer tube.","Using the handle of ","service tool T3880342"," remove the dust seal from the outer tube as shown below. Use a piece of cloth under the tool to prevent it from damaging the outer tube.","T3880342 - 17 mm U-Spanner","Dust seal","Cloth","Outer tube","Using a suitable tool, remove the circlip.","Note the orientation of the oil seal for installation.","Using the handle of ","service tool T3880342"," remove the oil seal. Use a piece of cloth under the tool to prevent it from damaging the outer tube.","T3880342 - 17 mm U-Spanner","Oil seal","Cloth","Remove the washer.","Washer","Outer tube"],"viewCount":0,"infoType":"InfoType11","createdAt":"2024-04-15T13:50:57.524Z","updatedAt":"2024-04-15T13:50:57.524Z","__v":0}